Privacy Policy for TronoTales
Effective Date: September 26, 2025

App Operator
This app is operated by [Your Name or Company Name], located in [City, Country].

Data Collection
TronoTales does not collect or transmit any personal data.
Usernames are freely chosen by players and are stored only locally on the device.
No data is stored, processed, or shared externally.

Camera Access
The camera is accessed solely to scan QR codes printed on official TronoTales game cards.
No images or scan data are transmitted or saved outside the device.

Gameplay Use
TronoTales is designed to support gameplay of the physical TronoTales game.
Use of the app is voluntary and at your own risk.
The developers are not liable for incorrect entries, scanning errors, or gameplay decisions made based on app usage.

Third-Party Services
TronoTales does not use any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services.
If such services are introduced in future versions, this Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly.

Content and Warranty
All content in TronoTales is provided “as is”, without any warranty, express or implied.

Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated effective date.

Contact Information
For any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact:
